Beulah is a senior curator of Coleoptera at the Natural History Museum, London. She has curatorial responsibility for the Carabidae, Cleroidea, Myxophaga and Archostemata as well as the Coleoptera larval collection. She is an experienced fieldworker focussed on developing the NHM collection of Neotropical Coleoptera. Her research interests also are focussed in the Neotropics in particular the systematics and evolution of the subfamily Lebiinae, a hyperdiverse group of predatory ground beetles.